Which specific health outcome indicators are listed under Sub-Domain 1.1: Key Outcomes in the Health Outcome Index guidebook?,"Under Sub-Domain 1.1: Key Outcomes, the listed indicators are Neonatal Mortality Rate (NMR), Infant Mortality Rate (IMR), Under-five Mortality Rate (U5MR), Teenage Fertility Rate, Proportion of Low Birth Weight (LBW) among newborns, and Sex Ratio at Birth (SRB).","[{""tool"": ""search_sharepoint_files"", ""args"": {""query"": ""A-Reference-Guidebook.docx""}}, {""tool"": ""read_sharepoint_file"", ""args"": {""item_id"": ""01C6LRSEIBAT2WVBKYQVG2KGNNEPJ23XUI""}}]",Web Search Apr26/A-Reference-Guidebook.docx,docx,None,False
"What are the recommended course options for Art majors at Elon University during their first semester, including both required and optional selections?","Art majors' first semester schedule includes the required courses ELN 1010: First Year Advising Seminar, and either COR 1100 or ENG 1100. They can choose up to one Studio Art class from options such as ART 1120 (Fundamentals of Design), ART 1140 (Time Arts), ART 2010 (Drawing I), ART 2020 (Painting I), or ART 2600 (Intro to Intermedia & Photography). Additionally, they can choose up to one Art History class from ARH 2100 (Art History of the Ancient World), ARH 2110 (Art History of Medieval and Premodern World), or ARH 2120 (Art History of the Modern World). It's important to note that Art majors do not need to take both an Art History and Studio Art class in their initial semester.","[{""tool"": ""search_sharepoint_files"", ""args"": {""query"": ""Art-2024-Guidebook.docx""}}, {""tool"": ""read_sharepoint_file"", ""args"": {""item_id"": ""01C6LRSEMRWRQAOFLJ4JFJ6JWG4OHGZ4UY""}}]",Web Search Apr26/Art-2024-Guidebook.docx,docx,None,False
What are some of the key characteristics that define Art Deco design?,"Key characteristics of Art Deco design include geometric shapes and symmetry (like zigzags, chevrons, triangles, and sunbursts), the use of luxurious materials such as marble, chrome, stainless steel, lacquer, ivory, exotic woods, gold, silver, and mirrored surfaces, bold color palettes with vibrant jewel tones, and influences from various global cultures, particularly Egyptian motifs.","[{""tool"": ""search_sharepoint_files"", ""args"": {""query"": ""artdeco.txt""}}, {""tool"": ""read_sharepoint_file"", ""args"": {""item_id"": ""01C6LRSEL4YV2Q6FU7KVE2XRFJDMLWUF6C""}}]",Web Search Apr26/artdeco.txt,txt,None,False
